text: Ignatyevsky () is a rural locality (a khutor) and the administrative center of Ignatyevskoye Rural Settlement of Koshekhablsky District, Adygea, Russia. The population of this khutor was 916 as of 2018. There are 19 streets. == Ethnicity == The Khutor is inhabited by Russians, Armenians, Adygheans, Avars, Uzbeks and Tatars. == References == Category:Rural localities in Koshekhablsky District
